# SnapTidy Project Rules

## Safety
- NEVER delete files — only move them
- NEVER enter .photoslibrary or .photolibrary directories
- Always get user confirmation before applying move plans
- Log all file operations to CSV audit trail
- Scan writes commit each entry immediately — zero data loss on crash

## Code Style
- Python 3.9+, PEP 8, 4-space indent
- CLI scripts use argparse with --input/--output/--index flags
- SQLite (.db) preferred for output; CSV as fallback
- All CSV files use UTF-8 with BOM for Excel compatibility
- No heavy dependencies (no pandas/numpy)

## Pipeline
1. scan_photos.py → photo_index.db (or .csv)
2. find_exact_duplicates.py / find_similar_photos.py → duplicates.csv
3. generate_move_plan.py → move_plan.csv
4. apply_move_plan.py → move_log.csv (requires user confirmation)
5. apply_move_plan.py --undo (reverse last operation)

## Interactive Workflow
organize_photos.py — one-command pipeline with step-by-step preferences

## Import
import_to_photos.py — import from external drives/Android into Photos.app with dedup
